==English==
===Etymology===
English ''[[walk]]'' + ''[[man]]''. The word '''walkman''' was made up to be the name of the Sony Corporation product described below, which first went on sale in Japan on July 1, 1979. '''Walkman''' remains to be a trademark in many countries, although it is now used for all sorts of portable music players independent of the manufacturer.
